what is docker images?
an image is a combination of a file system and parameters. Images contains the binaries ans dependencies.
Images container the data require to run the image.
for list out docker images
#docker images     command is used


docker images can be downloaded from docker hub.
Base images that have no parent image, usually images with an OS like Ubuntu,busybox or debian.
child images that build on base images and add additional fuctionality.
official images that are officially maintained and supported by docker.
user images that are created and shared by users like us. they build on base images and add additional functionality.
typically, these are formatted as user/image-name.


how to download images from repository to local host machine
#docker pull images name : image version

how to upload local image into docker repo
#docker image push image_name:tag